{
  "texts": [
    "I attended the rst of the law and economics programs Henry organized for federal judges and what was learned was so worthwhile that I attended two additional programs-this despite the fact that I regard myself as a social progressive and all the economists in attendance, from my perspective, had Neanderthal views on race and social policy.",
    "The basic lesson I learned, however, would have been forthcoming whatever the social outlook of the economist and that is that social good comes at a price, a social and economic cost.",
    "I had never thought that through before being exposed to Henry's teachings.",
    "While my views have not changed, the exposure to the thinking and teaching of the economists in these programs has led me to measure the cost of the social good being furthered against the gain to be achieved.",
    "I suppose what was learned amounts to social responsibility and required me to choose my priorities with greater care than before."
  ]
}